The paper proposes a deep learning approach for speaker recognition using a convolutional neural network and a self multi-head attention model. This work involves speech signal processing, feature extraction, and deep learning techniques, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.SD (Sound) is the most likely sub-category as it specifically deals with audio and speech processing. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as it involves natural language processing and speech recognition. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes a deep learning approach. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is possible as speaker recognition is often used in social network analysis. Finally, cs.SD is listed again as it is the most specific sub-category for this work.
